<!-- The problem we solve -->
<section class="about-block">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>THE PROBLEM WE SOLVE</h2>
    <p class="about-block-sub">A credential crisis in Nigerian hiring</p>
    <p>Nigerian universities produce hundreds of thousands of graduates each year. Employers from multinationals to fast-growing fintechs report the same problem: candidates arrive with degrees but without verifiable work records, documented research contributions, or professional endorsements from anyone who has actually worked with them.</p>
    <p>The result is an expensive, unreliable hiring process. Employers spend time and money assessing candidates whose capabilities cannot be independently confirmed. Graduates, meanwhile, are trapped in a market that cannot see their true worth.</p>
    <p>BridgeDegree replaces that uncertainty with proof. Our graduates do not ask employers to trust their word. They present a Career Passport, a verified, immutable, globally readable record of what they have done, who supervised it, and how they performed.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- The Career Passport -->
<section class="about-block">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>THE CAREER PASSPORT</h2>
    <p class="about-block-sub">A credential the world can read</p>
    <p>The Career Passport is BridgeDegree's core innovation. It is not a certificate. It is not a transcript. It is an authenticated, employer-readable record of a graduate's verified capabilities — assembled over years.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Work history — employer-verified, authenticated</li>
      <li>Published research — globally indexed, co-authored under supervision</li>
      <li>Performance reviews — structured, standardised, submitted by line managers</li>
      <li>Mentor endorsements — named senior professionals who supervised the work</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Any employer, anywhere in the world, can verify a BridgeDegree Career Passport in under 48 hours. The record is immutable — it cannot be edited, deleted, or falsified by the graduate or anyone else.</p>
  </div>
</section>

